.vboxclient-draganddrop-tty2-control.pid     .bash_history				  .bashrc    .vboxclient-clipboard-tty2-control.pid    .local
remark:
Lists entries in the order they're stored in the directory, without sorting them.
--------------------------------------------------------------
6)ls -g:
description:
  -g     like -l, but do not list owner
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ ls -g
total 44
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Desktop
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Documents
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 19 10:56 Downloads
drwxrwxr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 18 10:18 linx
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Music
drwxrwxr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 24 06:19 newc
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 18 10:27 Pictures
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Public
drwx------ 8 raakin 4096 Aug 18 10:33 snap
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Templates
drwxr-xr-x 2 raakin 4096 Aug 17 14:51 Videos
remark:
Produces a long format listing (-l) but omits the file's owner.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
7)ls -h:
description:
 -h, --human-readable
              with -l and -s, print sizes like 1K 234M 2G etc.
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ ls -h
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  linx  Music  newc  Pictures  Public  snap  Templates  Videos
remark:
When used with a long listing (-l), it prints file sizes in human-readable format (e.g., 1K, 234M, 2G).
------------------------------------------------------------------
8)ls -i:
description:
-i, --inode
              print the index number of each file
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ ls -i
1480371 Desktop  1480375 Documents  1480372 Downloads  1480657 linx  1480376 Music  1483040 newc  1480377 Pictures  1480374 Public  1480240 snap  1480373 Templates  1480378 Videos
remark:
Prints the inode index number to the left of each filename.

-------------------------------------------------------------------
9)ls -k:
description:
 -k, --kibibytes
              default to 1024-byte blocks for file system usage; used only with -s and per directory totals
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ ls -k
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  linx  Music  newc  Pictures  Public  snap  Templates  Videos
remark:
the ls -k command lists directory contents and shows file sizes in kilobytes.

------------------------------------------------------------------
