7)tree -l -L 1:
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ tree -l -L 1
.
├── Desktop
├── Documents
├── Downloads
├── linx
├── Music
├── newc
├── Pictures
├── Public
├── snap
├── Templates
└── Videos

12 directories, 0 files
remarks:
The command tree -l -L 1 in Linux displays the directory structure of the current directory (or specified directory) with the following specifics:
-l option: makes the command follow symbolic links as if they were directories.
-L 1 option: limits the depth of the tree output to only one level, showing only the immediate contents (files and subdirectories) of the specified directory without recursing further into subdirectories.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
