10)tree /var/log/apt -La 1 :
output:
raakin@ubuntu-25:~$ tree /var/log/apt -La 1
/var/log/apt
├── eipp.log.xz
├── history.log
└── term.log
remarks:
The command tree /var/log/apt -La 1 in Linux does the following:
tree: Displays the directory structure in a tree-like format.
/var/log/apt: Specifies the directory path to display.
-L 1: Limits the display depth to 1, showing only the contents of the specified directory (no subdirectories recursively).
-a: Includes all files, including hidden files (that start with a dot).
-l: Follows symbolic links as if they were directories.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

